    <item>
      <title>How to build a hashmap</title>
      <link>/posts/how_to_build_a_hashmap/</link>
      <pubDate>Thu, 06 Mar 2025 17:54:50 -0300</pubDate>
      
      <guid>/posts/how_to_build_a_hashmap/</guid>
      
      <description>&lt;p&gt;This week, we&amp;rsquo;re diving into one of the most powerful and fundamental data structures in programming: the Hash Map, often called a Hash Table or Dictionary. Hash maps are vital in nearly every language for quickly storing and retrieving data as key-value pairs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;What&amp;rsquo;s a Hash Map, Really?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A Hash Map is an array-based structure that gives you near-instant access to a stored value. It achieves this speed by using a special hash function to convert the key (e.g., a person&amp;rsquo;s name) into an index (a number) in the underlying array.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
    </item>
    
